version 1.0.0

 * license changed (1.9.3 Ruby's)
 * tested with Ruby 2.0.0-p0
 * fixed typo.

Merge pull request #1 from Spakman/master

Make ruby-termios work with Ruby/RubyGems 2.0.0

Move extension files to ext/ directory

Using Ruby 2.0.0-preview2 (RubyGems 2.0.0), the gem was failing to
install with this error:

  ...
  ...
  installing default termios libraries
  /usr/bin/install: `./lib/termios.rb' and `/path/to/gems/ruby-termios-0.9.6/lib/termios.rb' are the same file
  make: *** [/path/to/gems/ruby-termios-0.9.6/lib/termios.rb] Error 1

The solution, as pointed to by Kouhei Sutou[1], was to move extconf.rb
and termios.c to a new ext/ directory. This is in a similar manner to
the BigDecimal bug #7344[2].

1 - https://github.com/rubygems/rubygems/issues/411#issuecomment-11153724
2 - http://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/7344#note-6

Tested-by: Mark Somerville <mark@scottishclimbs.com> [F17, MRI 1.9.3/2.0.0-preview2]
Signed-off-by: Mark Somerville <mark@scottishclimbs.com>
version 0.9.6
removed rubygems_version

don't use File.mtime in gemspec

github reject it by $SAFE.
renamed to ruby-termios.gemspec from termios.gemspec
added RDoc and gemspec
removed "$Id$" line.

includes ruby/io.h instead of rubyio.h.

termios.c includes ruby/io.h instead of rubyio.h
for Ruby 1.9.x.  It is tested with Ruby 1.9.1RC1.

added ioctl() constants.

	* termios.c: added IOCTL_COMMANDS, IOCTL_COMMAND_NAMES,
	  MODEM_SIGNALS, MODEM_SIGNAL_NAMES, PTY_PACKET_OPTIONS,
	  PTY_PACKET_OPTION_NAMES, LINE_DISCIPLINES and
	  LINE_DISCIPLINE_NAMES.

	  This change is contributed from Chris Hoffman
	  <chrishoffman_cardialife.com>.

	* termios.c, extconf.rb: included <sys/ioctl.h>.

* extconf.rb, termios.c: adjusted rb_io_t/OpenFile checks for Ruby
  1.8.7.
rb_io_t test isnot needed for ruby1.6.
applied the patch from Akr-san.
applied a patch which makes ruby-termios work under both ruby1.8 and ruby1.9.  [ruby-talk:143781]
update README
version 0.9.4

now Termios::Termios is shadow of struct termios.
setattr and getattr convert between struct termios and Termios::Termios internally.

added new method Termios::Termios#set_cc.
added new constants Termios::{IFLAGS,OFLAGS,CFLAGS,LFLAGS,BAUD}.
rewrited tests and examples.
